title: Socceroos notify FIFA of security fears
text: SYDNEY — The Socceroos’ World Cup qualifier in Bangladesh next month was thrown into doubt Thursday when Football Federation Australia (FFA) officially notified FIFA of their security fears. With Cricket Australia calling off its tour of Bangladesh where two Tests were due to begin next Friday, Australia’s football chiefs announced their own concerns about playing in the South Asian nation. The group-topping Socceroos are due to take on Bangladesh in Dhaka on Nov. 17. The death of an Italian aid worker in Dhaka’s diplomatic quarter — shot three times Monday night in a murder claimed by Islamic State group — escalated safety fears. — AFP
